<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="434" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d434">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Italy/191a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Italy (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="to">Garrett</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 652</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-14">June 14,
                                    1932</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Secretary of State refers to previous correspondence regarding
                                the President’s Proposal of June 20, 1931, for postponement of
                                intergovernmental debts and transmits for the information of the
                                American Ambassador copy of the “Agreement between the Kingdom of
                                Italy and the United States of America, June 3, 1932”.<note n="60" xml:id="d434fn60">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Annual Report of the Secretary of the
                                        Treasury</hi>, 1932, pp. 295–296.</note>
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>